HEADWORD: Frumentaceous
<hw>Fru"men*ta"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frumentaceus</ets>, fr. <ets>frumentum</ets> corn or grain, from
the root of <ets>frux</ets> fruit: cf. F. <ets>frumentac⟦eacute⟧</ets>.
See <er>Frugal</er>.]</ety> <def>Made of, or resembling, wheat or other
grain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

